article.headline: Northern Iowa 69, Western Michigan 63
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) -- Erik Crawford scored 18 points to lead Northern Iowa to a 69-63 win over Western Michigan on Wednesday night. Grant Stout added 12 points and Ben Jacobson had 11 for Northern Iowa (2-0). Brian Snider led Western Michigan (1-1) with a career-high 26 points. He hit a game-high four 3-pointers, including three in the second half, as the Broncos attempted to come back from a 10-point deficit. Crawford, who scored just three points in the Panthers' season-opening victory over Western Carolina on Sunday, also had five assists and converted a game-high nine of 11 free throws. Northern Iowa made 61.9 percent (13-of-21) of its shots in the second half. Eric Coleman led the team with a game-high 11 rebounds, although the Panthers were outrebounded 37-34. Joe Reitz scored 12 for Western Michigan, and Derek Drews added 11 off the bench. Drews was held to one point in the second half after hitting two of three shots in the first half. Trailing by three points at halftime, Northern Iowa outscored the Broncos 14-2 in the first five minutes of the second half. Stout had three baskets in that stretch, and Western Michigan missed five of six shots.
